news.title: Swedish property firms should cut debt, raise equity: Riksbank Governor
news.para: Commercial property companies ramped up borrowing when rates were low and some are now struggling to pay off or roll-over debt after eight interest rate hikes by the central bank.

news.title: China's Logan Group seeks to postpone Dec 4 liquidation hearing: State media
news.para: The Shenzhen-based company said last year it would suspend interest payments and restructure its offshore debt including $3.7 billion in dollar bonds due to liquidity pressure.

news.title: Delhi civic body exempts house tax in residential areas across its rural jurisdiction
news.para: The Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD) will not collect any house tax from 'lal dora' or extended 'lal dora' properties in the rural areas, Oberoi told a press conference here.

news.title: SC directs Bihar government to ensure no further construction takes place adjacent to Ganga
news.para: ​A bench of Justices Aniruddha Bose and Augustine George Masih directed the state government to file an affidavit informing it about the removal of identified illegal structures, which have been raised on the floodplains of Ganga River in Patna.

news.title: Urban slums in Uttar Pradesh get a major development push
news.para: The programme focusses on development of underdeveloped and slum areas and currently 98 projects in seven districts are underway— Amhora, Deoria, Farrukhabad, Ayodhya, Mirzapur, Pilibhit and Ghaziabad.

news.title: Smart City works will be completed before next monsoon: Panaji MLA
news.para: City residents have been enduring inconveniences as several interior roads have been dug up since the works started over a year ago. The delays have only added to the woes of the people.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body may snap water supply to housing societies sans STPs
news.para: The move comes after these societies failed to respond to notices issued by the civic body in the past, urging them to activate their respective STPs.

news.title: I-T personnel search 20 premises of five builders in Sambhajinagar city
news.para: The premises included the builders’ residences, offices as well project sites. Sources said this was the second time one of the builders was raided by the I-T department in five years.

news.title: Indore's stamp & registrar department recovers Rs 7 crore
news.para: “In last six months, we have recovered at least Rs 7 crore in around 110 such cases” the senior district registrar Deepak Kumar Sharma said, adding that the department has identified around 300 people, who have more than Rs 1 lakh as due fees.

news.title: China Evergrande's creditors seek controlling stakes in new proposal
news.para: The group, which works as an ad hoc group of Evergrande's offshore creditors, made the request after the developer earlier this week made a new offer to repay their offshore debts, the source said.

news.title: Tenants urge government to get senior counsel to defend Maharashtra Rent Act in SC
news.para: In a letter to CM Eknath Shinde, the tenants have asked for a commitment to protect the rights of tenants, considering the history of rent control in the state and the actual payment of 'Pugree' by tenants.

news.title: Kolkata: Air-quality monitoring system now a must for razing buildings
news.para: ​​​Municipal commissioner Binod Kumar on Friday held an urgent meeting with KMC buildings department officials and asked them to sensitize developers about the need to adopt adequate measures to arrest dust particles rising from such activities.

news.title: Developers in Pune seek relaxation in pollution norms
news.para: The confederation officials said that any increase in the height of GI or metal sheets above 14 feet may create hindrance to light and ventilation of adjacent properties.

news.title: ED arrests 'agent' in Shine City money laundering case
news.para: The arrest comes as part of an ongoing investigation initiated by the ED based on approximately 250 FIRs registered by Uttar Pradesh Police against Rasheed Naseem and Shine City Group of Companies.

news.title: KK Rajeev Nambiar resigns as CEO of Shree Digvijay Cement Company
news.para: The board also approved appointment of Ramanujan Krishnakumar, currently working as senior vice president (Manufacturing), as an additional director, CEO & MD of Shree Digvijay Cement Company.

news.title: CPI Property Group commences internal audit after short-seller report
news.para: Short-selling hedge fund Muddy Waters last week disclosed its bet against the credit of CPI Property Group sending a key bond of the company to fall by the most on record.

news.title: Aldar Properties completes $291 million acquisition of London Square
news.para: "Aldar intends to leverage its expertise and balance sheet to support London Square's land acquisition strategy to enable it to develop larger and prime central London sites," the two companies said in a joint statement on Friday.
